Start Log 02:01

I would like to start this log off by saying that my prior actions are inexcusable. I failed to record events crucial to understanding my current situation. I apologize for this transgression. It will not happen again. I will now give a brief summary of what occurred.

Myself and my companion, another kidnapee, had discovered the remains of my gunship. Once I had determined that the ship would be unable to fly, I made my way back to the room I had awoken in. The correct course of action in this moment would have been to determine who or what had sabotaged my ride off this planet. But my emotions got the better of me. The destruction of the gunship also meant the destruction of ||Adam Malkovich's helmet.|| (You can read the Bottle Ship logs to learn more about why I had it with me.) The realization of this caused me to feel like a failure. I had failed to keep the only keepsake I had of ||him|| safe. As a result I felt like I had failed to live up to ||his|| expectations of me. This feeling haunted me as I slept in the recreation of my quarters.

When I awoke from my slumber the task before me was clear. My new mission was to gather information about this place to determine the who or what destroyed the gunship. Once again I searched the room. This time I looked not for what was missing, but what was there instead. It wasn't long until I discovered a note that I had missed.

```Hey there! Welcome to the Dream Home! I know it's a bit sudden to wake up in an odd place, but fret not; you don't have to worry. Your world isn't in danger, your world is safe; and when you return from here to your world, it'll resume as if you've never left! If you ever feel like it's a bit much hanging out here in this realm, with all of these other people from various worlds...Leave a complaint to Seteth and I'll deal with it eventually.```

GameInstance (an object spawned when you launch the application and that remains the same until you close it)
GameMode (spawned when a level is loaded)
GameState (spawned by the gameMode)
PlayerState (spawned when a PlayerController is spawned = when a player arrives in the game)

You have to pay close attention to what you do and where you do it when coding a multiplayer game. When it comes to singleplayer, you can't really "have it wrong" except for GameInstance stuff.

But here are the general guidelines I follow:
GameInstance - Holds any non-pointer persistent variables (persistent means that you need to store in between two levels and that you don't need to store in a SaveGame)
